{"id":14881702,"mediaExerciseId":"7b812803-00af-495c-b91d-036680d9abca","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"19A","chapterTitle":"Determining the Target Cash Balance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":672,"solutions":[{"id":6027108,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to determine the interest rate that Rise Against will use. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":60,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/91a6a07d23971353c91e0ec042a51f60/647fc0c908cf8ac090783c125e5376e1/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/91a6a07d23971353c91e0ec042a51f60/647fc0c908cf8ac090783c125e5376e1/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We have the following information about the Rise Against Corporation: Company has a fixed order cost in the amount of $F=\\$10$, the total cash needed for the year is $T=\\$31,000$. From the BAT model, the company has the  target cash balance of $\\$5,100$. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/91a6a07d23971353c91e0ec042a51f60/22066e74491d24e1a4658a431c0e2753/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/91a6a07d23971353c91e0ec042a51f60/22066e74491d24e1a4658a431c0e2753/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Using the given informations, and substituting them in the BAT model, we can caclulate the interest rate $R$ used by the company. So, \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Target cash balance}&=\\sqrt{\\frac{2\\cdot T\\cdot F}{R}}\\\\\n\\$5,100&=\\sqrt{\\frac{2\\cdot \\$31,000\\cdot \\$10}{R}}\\\\\n\\$5,100&=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\$620,000}{R}}\\\\\n\\$5,100^2&=\\frac{\\$620,000}{R}\\\\\n\\$26,010,000&=\\frac{\\$620,000}{R}\\\\\n\\Longrightarrow R&=\\frac{\\$620,000}{\\$26,010,000}\\\\\n&=0.0238\\hspace{2mm}\\text{or}\\hspace{2mm} 2.38\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the company must use an interest rate of $2.38$ percent per year.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"6c68b693-a6b7-47aa-a581-ea1ca732009a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881703,"exerciseName":"1","page":675,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d679df99-4bfd-4a07-936f-ed174578da5e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19a-exercises-1-d679df99-4bfd-4a07-936f-ed174578da5e"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881701,"exerciseName":"9","page":672,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b80d93d8-5168-47ed-8374-35746008758a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19a-exercises-9-b80d93d8-5168-47ed-8374-35746008758a"},{"id":14881700,"exerciseName":"8","page":672,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"46fe0674-5d1b-4a59-8c7a-683